Title: GUI Top
worldeditgui.common_commands.set.comment:
Perform the //set
Sets all the blocks in the region
worldeditgui.common_commands.copy.commen:
Copy the selection to the clipboard.
Perform the //copy
worldeditgui.common_commands.paste.comme:
Paste the clipboard’s contents
Perform the //past
worldeditgui.common_commands.move.commen:
Perform the //move [-abes] [multiplier] [offset] [-m <mask>]
Move the contents of the selection.
worldeditgui.common_commands.move_replac:
Perform the //move [-abes] [multiplier] [offset] [replace] [-m <mask>]
Move the contents of the selection.
worldeditgui.common_commands.rotate.comm:
Perform the //rotate
Rotate the contents of the clipboard.
Non-destructively rotate the contents of the clipboard.
Angles are provided in degrees and a positive angle will result in a clockwise rotation.
Multiple rotations can be stacked.
Interpolation is not performed so angles should be a multiple of 90 degrees.

worldeditgui.common_commands.stack.comme:
Perform the //stack [-abers] [count] [offset] [-m <mask>]
Repeat the contents of the selection.
worldeditgui.common_commands.flip.commen:
Perform the //flip [direction]
Flip the contents of the clipboard across the origin.
worldeditgui.hotkey.open_config.comment: The key open the in-game config GUI
worldeditgui.hotkey.add_init_integer.com: add init integer to the init change
worldeditgui.hotkey.decrease_init_intege: decrease init integer to the init change
worldeditgui.hotkey.message.add: Initial integer has been increased to:
worldeditgui.hotkey.message.decrease: Initial integer has been reduced to:
worldeditgui.generic.init_offset.comment: acceptable values are me to use facing direction, or any direction, or any block vector in the form x,y,z
worldeditgui.generic.init_direction.comm: acceptable values are 'me' to use facing direction, or any non-diagonal direction
worldeditgui.generic.init_s.comment: [-s] Shift the selection to the last stacked copy
worldeditgui.generic.init_m.comment: [-m <mask>] Set the include mask, non-matching blocks become air
worldeditgui.generic.init_mask.comment: <mask> Set the include mask, non-matching blocks become air
